=Perform the Canva find-and-replace automation using the following data.

Use the Canva design link provided and follow the system prompt instructions.

Canva Design URL:
https://www.canva.com/design/DAG2olfEo5o/b3eG0by8OUTkQm_rJSsIPg/edit

Data Sources:
- Old values (existing content in Canva) come from Google Sheets.
- New values (updated content) come from the `aggregator` node output.

Input Mapping:

Old Data (from Sheets):
Old Date: {{ $json.Date }}
Old Day: {{ $json.Day }}
Old Paragraph 1: {{ $json.news1 }}
Old Paragraph 2: {{ $json.news2 }}
Old Paragraph 3: {{ $json.news3 }}

New Data (from Aggregator Node):
New Date: {{ $('aggregator').item.json.Date }}
New Day: {{ $('aggregator').item.json.Day }}
New Paragraph 1: {{ $('aggregator').item.json.Headline1 }}
New Paragraph 2: {{ $('aggregator').item.json.Headline2 }}
New Paragraph 3: {{ $('aggregator').item.json.Headline3 }}

Execution Instructions:
- Replace all old values in Canva with the corresponding new values.
- Follow the step-by-step process defined in the system prompt (File ‚Üí Find and Replace ‚Üí Replace all).
- Process replacements in this order:
  1. Date (Old ‚Üí New)
  2. Day (Old ‚Üí New)
  3. Paragraph 1 (Old ‚Üí New)
  4. Paragraph 2 (Old ‚Üí New)
  5. Paragraph 3 (Old ‚Üí New)
- Wait appropriate delays between actions as per the system prompt.
- Confirm each replacement using Query.
- After all replacements are done, reload the design once and call End_Session.
